cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on centralized user association and spectrum allocation in heterogeneous networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper proposes optimization-based spectrum allocation schemes. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper studies centralized control on a slow timescale for joint optimization over multiple cells. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is possible as the paper mentions lower spectral efficiency and additional delays in data transmission. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions external interference levels in the unlicensed bands.
